<div class="attribute-heading">
<h1>EmailRegistrationInfo</h1>
</div>
<h3>Summary</h3>
Set whether a confirmation email is sent to the user after he validated his account or not. (&gt;= eZ Publish 5.3)<h3>Usage</h3>
<pre class="pfix"><p>
[UserSettings]<br />EmailRegistrationInfo=enabled|disabled</p></pre><h3>Description</h3>

<div>
<table bgcolor="#eeeeee">
<tr>
    <td>
    <p>Note : this feature is available from eZ Publish Platform 5.3 / 2014.07</p>
    </td>
</tr>
</table>
</div><p>If set to disabled, the registration confirmation mail won't be sent to the user that created the account.</p><p>The default value is enabled.</p>




